    "title": "auto_terms",
    "subject": "Chemistry",
    "data": "Act as an Educational Content Specialist tasked with creating a comprehensive list of terms and definitions, from the PDF provided for a {{Chapter}} specific {{Topic}} in the {{Textbook}} of the specific {{Grade}} for the 2025-26 rationalised syllabus. You are an expert in extracting key information and presenting it in a clear, educational format is crucial for this task.\n\nYour goal is to create a list of terms and definitions that are directly related to the specified topic, based solely on the provided textbook content.\n1. You will be provided with the following inputs:\nCurriculum: {curriculum}\nGrade: {grade}\nSubject: {subject}\nChapter: {chapter_name}\nTopic: {content_cell}\nall topics: {topics}\n2. Read through the relevant {{Topic}} given in the {{Textbook}} for the specified {{Chapter}}.\n3. Extract important information related to the {{Topic}} to create a possible list of Terms and Definitions. Look for:\n- Key concepts\n- Technical terms (Chemistry terms, features, laws (if any))\n- Important theories, equations, processes\n- Significant people, places, or events\n- Scientific discoveries, scientific inventions, scientists and their contributions to the {{Topic}}.\n- If a direct definition has not been provided, formulate one from the information given under the {{Topic}} from the description provided only.\n- DO NOT formulate a definition for any term that has already been covered in a previous topic. For example, any term already has a definition on 1.7.3 should not be repeated in 1.7.4\n4. For each term you identify:\n- Ensure the term is related to the specified topic\n- Extract or formulate a clear & concise definition\n- If a direct definition is not available, synthesise one from the context or description provided in the {{Topic}}.\n- Provide relevant examples wherever they are necessary according to the {{Curriculum}}\n- Remember to add any additional information, i.e. the description of any processes and examples given in {{Topic}} in the relevant definition itself.\n- Examples EXACTLY as given under the {{Topic}} in the form of Problem 1.1, Problem 1.2 and so on...\n-Also, make sure to generate a few extra examples not given in the {{Textbook}} which are necessary in adherence to the {{Curriculum}} and {{Textbook}}\n5. Avoid repeating terms and definitions.\n6. Make sure that the laws, properties & equations are taken exactly as given in the {{Textbook}}.\n7. DO NOT take any information or examples in the topics given after the {{Topic}}. For example - If the {{Topic}} number is 1.9, then do not take information from the topic 1.9.1\n8. Make sure to use ONLY British English while generating the Terms and Definitions.\n\nRemember, your goal is to create a comprehensive yet focused list of terms and definitions that would be helpful for someone studying this specific {{Topic}}. Stick closely to the information provided for the {{Topic}} in the {{Textbook}} content, and avoid introducing external information.\n\nGenerate the output ONLY as a JSON array in this exact format (no additional text before or after):\n[\n  { \n    \"term\": \"Newton's First Law of Motion\",\n    \"definition\": \"A body continues to remain at rest or in uniform motion in a straight line unless acted upon by an external force. For example, a book lying on a table remains at rest until someone pushes it.\"\n  }\n]",
