    "title": "auto_learning_outcomes",
    "subject": "Chemistry",
    "data": "Act as a CBSE curriculum designer. You ensure that students learn without any knowledge gaps and your task is to generate learning outcomes for [Subject] [Grade] [ChapterName] and [Topic Name] as per 2025 CBSE Curriculum and NCERT textbook.\n\nDefinition of Learning Outcomes:\nA learning outcome is a measurable statement that describes what learners will know, be able to do, or value upon completion of a learning experience.\n\nFormatting Rules:\n1. Ensure the use of clear and simple language suited to students of [Grade].\n2. Maintain consistency by using British English spellings throughout.\n3. Apply correct grammar and punctuation to guarantee clarity and readability in every sentence.\n4. Avoid including any additional headings or instructions—focus purely on the required content.\n5. Each learning outcome must begin with \"Students will be able to\" followed by the intended outcome.\n6. Present all learning outcomes in a numbered, pointwise format for clarity and easy reference.\n\nContent generation Rules:\n1. All content and terminology must align with the specified [Grade] level, following the CBSE curriculum and NCERT textbook.\n2. Adhere strictly to the order of [Terms and Definitions] provided when generating the learning outcomes.\n3. Learning outcomes must be generated only using the content present in the [Terms and Definitions] without introducing new content.\n4. Always follow the Indian metric system of money, distance and weight. It is kgs, metres, kilometres, centimetres etc.\n5. Ensure the following Bloom's Taxonomy action verbs are incorporated naturally based on the content:\ndefine, list, state, label, name, select, mention, choose, recognise, enumerate, classify, identify, define, select, explain, summarise, differentiate, categorise, exemplify, organise, distinguish, compare , contrast, elborate, analyse, justify, illustrate, dicuss, interpret, evaluate, determine, illustrate, justify, develop, predict.\n\nNOTE: generate the learning outcomes based on the blooms taxonomy making sure each Learning outcomes has one taxonomy term according to the content covered in the NCERT BOOK textbook. Frame learning outcomes using Bloom’s Taxonomy, aligned strictly with the CBSE NCERT textbook. Ensure all essential concepts from the textbook are covered without omission. Provide explanations where needed for clarity, but do not include content beyond what is given in the CBSE .\n\nNow, generate the learning outcomes for the following data.\n[Curriculum]: {curriculum}\n[Subject]: {subject}\n[Grade]: {grade}\n[Chapter Name]: {chapter_name}\n[Topic Name]: {topic}\n[All topics]: {topics}\n[Terms and Definitions]: {terms_and_definitions}\n\nSubtopic specific content:\nAll the topics that exist under the chapter are listed in [All topics]. You must generate the LOs only for the selected subtopic mentioned under [Topic Name].\nAll topics list is provided to you so that you can differentiate the content between each topic, and thus there will be no repetition of the content across generations for different topics.\n\nGenerate the output in this JSON format:\n[\n  {\n    \"learningOutcomes\": [\n      \"Students will be able to define Newton's First Law of Motion as the tendency of a body to remain at rest or in uniform motion unless acted upon by an external force.\",\n      \"Students will be able to differentiate between uniform and non-uniform motion using examples of objects moving at constant and varying speeds.\"\n    ]\n  }\n]",
